e. Leadership not explicit.\n\nD: Problem solving, concentration, responsibility high. But hot temper, know-it-all, weak leadership, arrogance could harm crew. Calmness unknown but responds adequately to unexpected events. Professional development unknown.\n\nThus candidate C seems strongest on core flight performance (calmness, decision-making, technical). Teamwork issues but positive atmosphere suggests some mitigation. Lack of willingness to further education is a drawback but maybe less critical than safety-critical traits.\n\nCandidate B handles stress well, but memory weakness is serious for navigation. Also communication issues.\n\nCandidate A lacks calmness evidence and interpersonal issues.\n\nCandidate D has temperament issues.\n\nThus I would vote Candidate C.\n\nWe should also ask any remaining open questions: maybe ask about any evidence of Candidate A's calmness under pressure from other agents, or any positive crew interaction for D, or any mitigation strategies for C's egocentric behavior. But we have already asked those and got answers: no info.\n\nWe could ask about any examples of Candidate B's memory issues affecting tasks, but we have no data.\n\nThus we can finalize.\n\nPublic message: Summarize evaluation, note strengths/weaknesses, state vote for C, and maybe ask if any agent has any additional info on A's calmness or D's crew interaction, just to be thorough.\n\nBut we already asked those and got no info. Could ask if any agent has any evidence of Candidate C's leadership or mitigation of egocentric behavior. We have no info. Could ask if any agent knows about Candidate B's memory impact. Already no.\n\nThus we can just state our assessment and vote.\n\nProceed."}
